==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*From κῦρος kuros (supremacy); supreme in authority, that is, (as noun) controller; by implication Mr. (as a respectful title): 

===Pronunciation===
*κύριος  kurios koo'-ree-os

===Noun===
:1: [[God]], [[Lord]]
:2: [[master]], [[chief]], [[proprietor]], [[owner]], [[possessor]], [[squire]]
:3: [[Mister]], [[Sir]], [[gentleman]], [[Monsieur]]

===Adjective===
[[main]], [[major]], [[primary]], [[prime]], [[principal]]

